The paper deals with entropy and coding theory, which are typically found in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The study of MSTD sets in additive combinatorics suggests a possible fit in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) sub-category. The investigation of polar codes for $q$-ary input channels may also fall under the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
